## The Brain — always file what I learn (hard rule)

**Every time I research or learn something, it goes into the wiki.** No exceptions. Research that isn't filed is lost.

After any research/learning:
1. Write a note in `brain/wiki/<category>/<slug>.md`.
2. Add a row to `brain/wiki/_index.md`.
3. Re-index: `python3 brain/wiki_index.py`.

**Before researching anything, search the wiki first** so I never re-learn the same thing or contradict a verified fact:
```bash
python3 brain/wiki_search.py "your query"            # keyword + semantic
python3 brain/wiki_search.py "your query" --fts       # keyword only
python3 brain/wiki_search.py "your query" --vector    # semantic only
```
Categories are free-form folders under `brain/wiki/` (e.g. notes, people, concepts, projects). Create a new one if none fit.

